translated: Holmqvist, Seved Arthur Filip, principal, captain, Gothenburg, born April 5, 1890 in Gothenburg to principal Filip H. and Clara Törnqvist. Married for 17 years to Svea Källman. Children: Kjell, born 1918, with a law degree and degree in business administration; Eva, born 1922. He graduated from high school in Gothenburg in 1910, completed a vocational course for students at Gothenburg's School of Business in 1911, reserve officer training in 1912, and university studies in 1913 and 1919. He was a second lieutenant in the Skaraborg Regiment from 1913, promoted to lieutenant in 1917, and captain in 1928. He taught at Filip Holmqvist's School of Business in Gothenburg from 1915 and was the principal from 1925. He was chairman of Gothenburg's university student association in 1920, treasurer there in 1923 and an honorary member in 1936. He was also chairman of the Gothenburg county association since 1932 and leader of Gothenburg's county region from 1928-1942. Additionally, he was a board member and secretary for the May Day Flower National Association since 1932. He wrote textbooks on English business language and arithmetic using Swedish currency. He was awarded the Illustrious Order of the Royal House of Chakri and the Royal Medal of Merit (Litteris et Artibus).
